==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Walling
<hw>Wall"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of making a
wall or walls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Walls, in general; material for walls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Walling wax</b></col>, <cd>a composition of wax and
tallow used by etchers and engravers to make a bank, or wall, round the
edge of a plate, so as to form a trough for holding the acid used in
etching, and the like.</cd> <rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Walloons</ent>⟦br⟧
